Sustainable Development Goal 3: Good Health and Wellbeing

Product Vision:
To provide a seamless and digital first healthcare experience for university community that
eliminates manual booking delays, ensures evenhanded access to medical professionals and also
promotes proactive health management through the innovative appointment system.

System Problem and Solution:

The current university clinic processes usually rely on manual walk ins or phone calls that lead to
long waiting times and scheduling conflicts for students with tight class timetables while also
overloading the administration of the clinic. The solution that this project showcases is a
centralized Clinic Appointment System that allows students to view real time doctor availability
and manage their own health schedules while also providing administrators and doctors with
automated tools to manage the patient flow in the clinic.
